TY  - JOUR
AB  - Applicants for Social Security Disability Benefits who fail to pass the medical screening form a natural `control' group for beneficiaries. Data drawn from the 1972 and 1978 surveys of the disabled done for the Social Security Administration show that fewer than 50 percent of rejected male applicants work. These data cast doubt on recent econometric work which suggests that the disincentive effects of DI have been substantial.
